It was a large crowd of 55 people for most of the discussions, only 13 participants responded and actively engaged. The rest of them were merely just present for the meeting. The meeting was facilitated by the DIET Principal which is not listed in the option and hence I selected the External Option. The data from google forms were analysed and presented with all the DIET Lecturers, BRPs and CRPs. It was really amazing to see the Principal lead discussion based on data. Some of my observations from the discussion were.
1. The Principal asked qualitative reflections from the officials to dig deep on the quantitative data collected.
2. The Principal presented reflections connecting with the multiple questions to understand the holistic picture of implementation.
This data based discussion happened for almost for 2 and half hours for the entire first half.

remarks:
Goodmorning everyone,
Yesterday I have been to Gadag ( District Progress Review meeting)

This is one of the best progress review meeting i have attended.

Some of the highlights are as follows.
Well planned and executed the session as per agenda by @‚Å®Radder DIET Lecturer Gadag‚Å© (Mr Honna Radi -Radder sir)

All the BEOs, BRCs are present. 100% attendence. They are not just presented their best practices. They took the initiative of leading DPRM by each block. ( hence, participants wont find challenging in transportation, food and other things for effective meeting) there is excellent ownership by every block.

Nearly 120+ officials are participated.
Interestingly speeches are completed before 11:30 AM.

During the meeting, everyone are proactively participated, shared their reflections, well documented of each and every activity for example success stories, classroom observations , discussed, FAQs and reflected on the videos, 

There was huge appreciation by DIET principal sir and @‚Å®Radder DIET Lecturer Gadag‚Å© sir to the participants.
They also shared the feedback where to improve. They decided the priorities to keep in mind.

Moving a head lot of interesting energiser like quiz, nalli kalli dance.üòçüòç

At the end of the meeting when we asked them to reflect on DSERT-STiR district progress review meeting structure.
Two highlights of the meeting
1 Area of improvement.

Everyone shared we have covered all the aspects of DPRM structure.
They also shared we could have shared more success stories.

Overall it was a best meeting i ever attend.

Thankyou DIET principal sir and @‚Å®Radder DIET Lecturer Gadag‚Å© sir for the opportunity.


Thanks and Regards
Gopala krishna s
Belgavi region
STIR Education
